value.0: This pale elven man is, somewhat creepily, devoid of any body hair. He regards you with a neutral expression as you draw near his makeshift research station.

Value.value: I am researching a somewhat strange phenomenon; something has drawn an entire swarm of mephits to the foothills north of here.
You waste my time with a lack of results? Begone and do not return until you have something of interest to show me!
Ah, interesting. This crystal originates from the Elemental Plane of Earth. It almost has a magnetic quality. My thanks. You have done well.
The area is far too dangerous for myself, but if you show me anything of interest that you come across, you will be rewarded in kind.
Should you find any more of these crystals, do not expend them. They may be of greater use.

value.0: This woman looks like a keen shot. She watches over the nearby scholar boredly.
The Obsidian Guard are renowned for their skill and are dangerously organized.

This helmet has been exquisitely forged from adamantine, its sinisterly beautiful design typical of drow craftsmanship. A small letter "V" has been interwoven into the pattern upon the visor.

Adamantine is an extraordinarily hard alloy that is almost impenetrable to normal weapons. Deposits of adamant are usually found near areas of Faerzress in the Underdark, and to the Deep Denizens it is usually black in colour, though it possesses a green sheen when viewed by natural light or a purple-white sheen when viewed by magical light.
